oai_dc:dc.dc:title: PROBLEMS WITH SMALL CRAFT HARBORS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Noble, H. Morgan
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: small craft harbors
marina design
mooring
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Administration of a small craft harbor includes, among its problems, those of finance, law, public relations, policing, and engineering. This paper will relate experiences in all of these categories, but as it is written for Coastal Engineers, it will cover the engineering category most completely.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 6 (1957): Proceedings of 6th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Gainesville, Florida, 1957.; 38
